    <h2>About the Women's Ministry</h2>
    <p>The Shiloh Women's Ministry is growing each year! Our women are reaching out to each other and building Christian relationships. The current members of Shiloh are embracing the new members and getting them involved with the Women's Ministry and with the church as a whole. Come and join the Shiloh Women's Ministry and be blessed with prayer, teaching, and spiritual growth!   Loretha Davis, Shiloh Women's Ministry Director</p>
    <img alt="Picture" src="http://www.shiloh2000.net/shiloh/Ministries/Ministry/a_Rectangle_143.gif" />

    <h2>Senior Women's Ministry</h2>
    <p>Barbara Topps is leader of the Senior Ministry. This group of women attend the Shiloh Baptist Church Senior Prayer, Fellowship and Bible Study classes every Wednesday at 11:00 PM. Lunch is provided every third Wednesday. There are many events scheduled for 2006. Please call Barbara at 276-6609 if you would like to join the Shiloh Senior Ministry and for more information about any of these upcoming events!</p>
    <img alt="Picture of Barbara Topps" src="http://www.shiloh2000.net/shiloh/Ministries/Ministry/Women_s/a_Topps-Barbara1.jpg" />

    <h2>Tea & Chocolate Ministry</h2>
    <p>Brenda Cheathon is the leader of the Tea & Chocolate Ministry. These women from ages 36 to 60+ will be meeting each second Sunday at 5:00 PM. This is an accountability and care group. Please call for meeting locations at 276-6609. The May 14th gathering is being rescheduled due to Mother's Day. A new date will be announced in the Sunday morning church bulletin.</p>
    <img alt="Picture of Brenda Cheathon" src="http://www.shiloh2000.net/shiloh/Ministries/Ministry/Women_s/a_Mrs_Brenda_Cheathon2.png" />
    
    <h2>Young Women Ministry</h2>
    <p>Mildred Riley is the leader of the Young Women Ministry. These women from ages 18-35 will be meeting each second Sunday at 5:00 PM. The remainder of the meetings for 2006 will be: April 9, May 6 (overnight lock-in at the Youth Ministry Center), September 10, October 8, November 12 and December 10. Please call for meeting locations at 276-6609.</p>

    <h2>Young Teen Ministry</h2>
    <p>Brenna Spence is the leader of the Young Teen Ministry. These girls are in 6th-12th grades. The Teen Ministry has gotten off to a great start this year with activities such as the: Jan. 28th Cooking Class, Feb. 24th Theater, March 31st Gathering at Shiloh. Future events include: April 23rd "Women Mentoring Generations", Mother's Day Luncheon on May 13th, and the June 9th School's Out Seward Trip. Please call if you want more information or to join the Young Teen Ministry at 276-6609.</p>

    <h2>Young Girls Ministry</h2>
    <p>Cassandra Autry is the leader of the Young Girls Ministry. These girls are in grades K-5. The Young Girls met in January and February, and on March 25th for crocheting. Future events include: April 29th - Baking, May 20th - Ice Skating, September 30th - Welcome Back, October 31st - Harvest Fest, November 18th - Fruit Baskets and Delivery to the Nursing Home, and December 16th - Gift Making. Please call if you want more information or to join the the Young Girls Ministry at 276-6609.</p>

    <h2>Roundtable Reading Group</h2>
    <p>Regina Toussant is the leader of the Roundtable Reading Group Ministry. The format is designed for simultaneous group readings of a book each month The group then gets together to discuss the book; their primary goals are Christian growth, analysis and fellowship.</p>
    <p>The next meeting dates will be held on April 29, May 27, June 24, September 23, October 28 and December 9. Please call 276-6609 for more information.</p>

